    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This episode contains three parts: news coverage, a report on a Chinatown tenant-landlord dispute, and a feature report on ethnic discrimination in the United States. The first part is a CCTV news report which covers international, national, and local news. The second part is a report about a dispute between Chinatown tenants and the landlord called Thomas Sung (孫啟誠). The third part features the history and current status of Chinese Americans and Asian Americans being discriminated against and stereotyped. The feature starts from the launch of a Yves Saint Laurent produced perfume called Opium. Interviews with experts and clips from the documentary The Fist of Righteous Harmony are also included. The host criticizes discrimination and stereotypes.</field>
